disadvantaged </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">students and their more advantaged peers is higher than the average </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">and</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> the attainment gap between these two groups is much smaller. </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">These students also make </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">faster</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> progress</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> between Key Stage 2 and Key Stage 4</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">, on average, than other </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">students nationally.</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">n some regions of the country, disadvantaged students are falling behin</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">d their more advantaged peers. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">In Yorkshire and the Humber,</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">attainment gap</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">’ between disadvantaged </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">Year 11 </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">students and their more advantaged peers in converter academies</span><span style="font-fami